6.00	Mistress_of_the_Animals	Potnia Theron	Potnia Theron (Ἡ Πότνια Θηρῶν, "Mistress of the Animals") is a term first used (once) by Homer (Iliad 21. 470) and often used to describe female divinities associated with animals. The word Potnia, meaning mistress or lady, was a Mycenaean word inherited by Classical Greek, with the same meaning, which has an exact parallel in Sanskrit .	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f4/NAMA_Art%C3%A9mis_Orthia.jpg/150px-NAMA_Art%C3%A9mis_Orthia.jpg
